						<summary>

						<p>This record belongs to the reign of the Yādava king <hi rend="bold">Kandharadēva</hi> and is dated in the 5th year of his reign, the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Sādhāraṇa, Pushya, ba. 30, Vyatīpāta</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Śravaṇa,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1250 January 4</hi> on which day Uttarāshāḍha was current till ·53 of the day and Śravaṇa began after that. It registers the gift of Siṅganahāḷu to the <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Bāguḷi</hi> by <hi rend="bold">Jannamarasa</hi> under the orders <hi rend="bold">Chavuḍiseṭṭi.</hi></p>						

